 poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs David Lochore was born about 1270, in Scotland. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir David Drumry of Lochore."},"et":{"about 1270–":"umbes 1270–Surnud","1265–1295":"1265–1295","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1300":"1300","1265":"1265","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochore Castle, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Lochore, Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1270–":"noin 1270–Kuollut","1265–1295":"1265–1295","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","about 1270":"noin 1270","1300":"1300","1265":"1265","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochore Castle, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Lochore, Fife, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1270–":"environ 1270–Décédée","1265–1295":"1265–1295","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","about 1270":"environ 1270","1300":"1300","1265":"1265","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Écosse","Lochore Castle, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Lochore, Fife, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs David Lochore est née environ 1270, à Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sir David Drumry of Lochore."},"de":{"about 1270–":"um 1270–Verstorben","1265–1295":"1265–1295","1300–Female":"1300–Verstorben","1270–Female":"1270–Verstorben","about 1270":"um 1270","1300":"1300","1265":"1265","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochore Castle, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Lochore, Fife, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Mrs David Lochore wurde um 1270 in Scotland geboren. Sie hatte mit Sir David Drumry of Lochore mindestens 1 Tochter."}